By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Senate, Tuesday, passed for concurrence, the National Youth Service Corps Trust Fund Bill 2022. Also passed were three other bills to establish the Institute of Credit Administration; Federal University of Agriculture and Entrepreneurship Saki; and Repeal and Re-enact the Pharmacy Council of Nigeria Act. The bills were sponsored by the Deputy Senate Leader, Ajayi Boroffice (APC, Ondo North). The four bills for concurrence, from the House of Representatives, were all passed by the upper chamber, after a clause-by-clause consideration by the Committee of the Whole. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Senate has passed a bill for concurrence seeking to establish the National Assembly Library Trust Fund.  Also passed for concurrence were three other bills namely, Nigerian Council for Management Development Bill, 2022; Animal Health and Husbandry Technologists Registration Board (Establishment) Bill, 2022;… In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Senate has passed the Chatered Institute of Forensic and Fraud Examiners of Nigeria bill and three others for concurrence. The bills were passed moments before the upper chamber adjourned plenary on Tuesday. The four bills for concurrence were sponsored by the Senate… In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Senate, on Tuesday, passed four bills to establish Federal Medical Centres in four states of the federation.The medical centers will be established in Osogbo, Osun State; Onitsha, Anambra State; Gada, Sokoto State; and Ijebu-Ode, Ogun State, respectively.  The passage of the bills… In "Top Stories"